# ─── UnicornX Aleo Frontend — Environment Variables ───
# Copy to `.env` (or `.env.local`) and run `npm run build` / `npm run dev`.
# Vite only exposes vars prefixed with `VITE_` to the client bundle.

# ─── API base URL ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Leave BLANK in dev so requests go through the Vite proxy (see
# vite.config.ts — proxies /api to http://localhost:5170). Set this in
# production builds so the static bundle hits the live backend.
#
# Production:
#   VITE_API_URL=https://aleo.unicornx.fun
# Local dev (optional — blank also works thanks to the proxy):
#   VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:5170
VITE_API_URL=

# ─── Aleo chain config (mirrors server/.env) ────────────────────────────
# Used by wallet/transition calls inside the browser.
VITE_PROGRAM_ID=unicornx_v3.aleo
VITE_NETWORK=testnet
VITE_ENDPOINT=https://api.explorer.provable.com/v1
